<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-01-08T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-01-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.1718/108: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-08T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 8,
                                        1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>3. Your 9, January 7, 4 p.m. Please cable full text of note when
                            received. You may inform Solorzano informally that this Government <pb facs="0703" n="621" xml:id="pg_621"/> will give note most careful
                            consideration. Inquire whether there is any objection to publication of
                            note.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>